Hello I can' get past the zip codes

Hi there! It sounds like you're having trouble with the zip code targeting in your ad setup. Could you please provide more details about the issue? Are you unable to enter the zip codes, or is there an error message appearing? Let me know so I can assist you better!
I am getting an error. I can add the zip codes but then it asked for the city, state

Thanks for the details! It seems like there might be a requirement to specify the city and state along with the zip codes for targeting. Make sure you're entering all three: zip code, city, and state. If you're still facing issues, try refreshing the page or clearing your browser cache. If the problem persists, please let me know!
I need to add 70 zip codes

Adding multiple zip codes can be a bit tricky! You might want to try entering them in batches or using a CSV file if the platform supports it. If you're still having trouble, double-check that each zip code is correctly formatted and corresponds to the right city and state. If you need further assistance, feel free to reach out!
It takes the zip codes but then asks for city and stste

It sounds like the system requires both city and state information for each zip code you enter. You might need to manually input the city and state for each zip code, or check if there's an option to upload a file with all the details. If this is causing issues, try contacting support at adsupport@newsbreak.com for more detailed assistance.
I'm here to help! Could you please provide more details about the issue you're facing? Whether it's related to zip codes, ad setup, or something else, let me know so I can assist you better.

To add zip codes, you should be able to enter them directly into the targeting section of your ad setup. If you're being prompted for city and state as well, make sure to input those details for each zip code. If you're adding a large number of zip codes, check if there's an option to upload them via a CSV file or similar method. If you continue to face issues, please reach out to adsupport@newsbreak.com for further assistance.

I understand, it can be frustrating when things don't work as expected. If there's anything specific you need help with or if there's a particular step that's causing trouble, just let me know and I'll do my best to assist you!
